# Fix Notes - Lesson 1

## Root Cause
The application used the `node-serialize` library, which allows execution of functions embedded in JSON via the `$$ND_FUNC$$` marker.

This allowed attackers to inject and execute arbitrary code.

## Fix Applied
- Removed `node-serialize`
- Replaced with safe `JSON.parse()`
- Wrapped parsing in try-catch
- Added strict validation on input fields

## Why This Fix Works
- `JSON.parse()` does not execute functions
- Malicious payloads are treated as invalid input
- The backend no longer evaluates user-controlled code

## Result
- RCE is prevented
- Malicious payloads are rejected safely
